  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.6.0-stable-facc47cb`\r\nOS & Version: Linux Mint 18.1 (4.4.0-53-generic)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nNetwork ID is said to be a 64 bit unsigned integer, so if the network ID fits this requirement, everything should be working correctly.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nAdding peers (through --bootnodes key or through admin.addPeer in the console) becomes impossible when networkId doesn't fit signed int. I reviewed the actual master branch and it seems like there is an inconsistency in the type of networkId in different places (I've seen uint64, uint32 and int as well).\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1. Launch geth with a large networkId value (I used `geth --port 30303 --datadir data --networkid 48314142015 --ipcdisable --nodiscover --verbosity 6 console`).\r\n1. Start a new node on an another port: `geth --port 30304 --datadir data_second --networkid 48314142015 --ipcdisable --nodiscover --verbosity 6 console`\r\n1. From the new node connect to the first node: `admin.addPeer(\"enode://6e5d0ca547f9cf48185da4c7821222c5a0dd1715f9123634f28ab01abf96225a3813e5990bdd227cb6b3a933440091859efb39fe0ba0610447bb9f011723750d@[::]:30303?discport=0\")`\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\nTRACE[04-20|14:24:10] New dial task                            task=\"staticdial 6e5d0ca547f9cf48 127.0.0.1:30303\"\r\nDEBUG[04-20|14:24:10] Adding p2p peer                          id=6e5d0ca547f9cf48 name=Geth/v1.6.0-stable-f... addr=127.0.0.1:30303 peers=1\r\nTRACE[04-20|14:24:10] Dial task done                           task=\"staticdial 6e5d0ca547f9cf48 127.0.0.1:30303\"\r\nTRACE[04-20|14:24:10] New dial task                            task=\"wait for dial hist expire (29.999996337s)\"\r\nTRACE[04-20|14:24:10] Starting protocol eth/63                 id=6e5d0ca547f9cf48 conn=staticdial\r\nDEBUG[04-20|14:24:10] Ethereum peer connected                  id=6e5d0ca547f9cf48 conn=staticdial name=Geth/v1.6.0-stable-facc47cb/linux-amd64/go1.8.1\r\nDEBUG[04-20|14:24:10] Ethereum handshake failed                id=6e5d0ca547f9cf48 conn=staticdial err=\"NetworkId mismatch - 1069501759 (!= 48314142015)\"\r\nTRACE[04-20|14:24:10] Protocol eth/63 failed                   id=6e5d0ca547f9cf48 conn=staticdial err=\"NetworkId mismatch - 1069501759 (!= 48314142015)\"\r\nDEBUG[04-20|14:24:10] Removing p2p peer                        id=6e5d0ca547f9cf48 conn=staticdial duration=658.15Âµs peers=0 req=false err=\"NetworkId mismatch - 1069501759 (!= 48314142015)\"\r\n````\r\n",
